About Hawaiian Village
55+ Active Living in Ideal Southwest Florida Mobile Home Community!
Situated on the west coast of Florida, Hawaiian Village is a little corner of paradise. Our tropical property is nestled on 50 beautiful acres with 265 lots that offers the perfect mix of a Hawaiian resort and classic Polynesian hospitality.
Surrounded by beautiful beaches, gardens, and wildlife preserves, residents and vacationers alike have the choice of many area attractions to explore.
Or stay at home and enjoy the community activities and lifestyle, which includes a huge sparkling in ground heated pool, a beautiful recreation center, a library, game room, shuffleboard, and so much more.
Robinson Preserve
Nationally recognized as the areas #1 family activity, the Robinson Preserve provides fun for the entire family. The preserve consists of 682 acres that is a mix of mangroves and tidal marsh.
Beaches
Florida’s warm, sandy west coast beaches are just a short drive away.
Area Golf
Semi-private and Municipal Golf Clubs, including IMG Academy Golf Club, Timber Creek Golf Course, Manatee County Golf Course, and River Run Golf Links.
Myakka River State Park
Myakka River flows through a vast expanse of unspoiled wetlands, prairies and pinelands that make up Myakka River State Park. Boating, fishing, canoeing and kayaking are popular activities here.
.
The John and Mable Ringling Museum of Art
The Ringling, the State Art Museum of Florida, is home to one of the preeminent art and cultural collections in the United States.
